This paper discusses the resource management and scheduling policies in Apache Mesos, which is a distributed system and falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the fairness and allocation of resources, which can be related to System and Control (cs.SY) and Operating Systems (cs.OS). The paper also mentions the use of different frameworks such as Apache Aurora and Marathon, which can be related to Networked and Internet Systems (cs.NI) and Performance (cs.PF).
